==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sextuple
<hw>Sex"tu*ple</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Formed (in
imitation of <ets>quadruple</ets>) fr. L. <ets>sextus</ets> sixth: cf.
F. <ets>sextuple</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Six times as much;
sixfold.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Divisible by six; having six
beats; <as>as, <ex>sixtuple</ex> measure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sexual</ent>⟦br⟧
